title: Seth Chen’s Resume
text:
isaac@applesdofall.org | My wikipedia page



brigham Young University-Idaho2022-Present - BS Computer Science - Data Scinece | Software Design Certificate - GPA: 3.91 - Data Science Group Member | BYU-I Data Science Society.




C++
Python
SQL





Implemented Apollo Lander Simulator and Artillery Simulator, concentrated on requirement elicitation skills, pair programming skills, and applying related physics.
Assisted 1 professor’s research at BYU-I, focused on finding recommendations for program modularization for people at different levels.









Retrieved necessary data from Canvas API to Google Sheets by writing 10 optimized and reusable Google Appscript codes to handle requests from course builders.

Brought all data and processes into one place by building 1 Canvas App to simplify office’s hiring process.

Kept up continuing personal value in the team by setting and following up weekly goals to bring value, leading to a constantly growing team.

Socialized within the team by attending 10 team activities to build up relationships and trust.








Simplified complex working flow by communicating with the team and documenting details of each ticket to handle various technical requests around campus, leading to better teamwork proficiency.

Provided 55 customers personalized assistance by offering available timeframe and observing what might be needed while calling.

Conducted testing procedures created by former technicians and developed new ones based on personal experience to troubleshoot computers and peripherals.
